# Error Handling

- Fail safely and predictably.
- For server actions and endpoints: validate input first, check auth second, perform mutation third, return structured errors.
- Do not swallow Supabase errors silently.
- Log server-side when useful, but never log secrets or tokens.
- Surface actionable user-facing errors without revealing internals.

# API / Endpoint Rules

- If creating SvelteKit API routes: keep them server-only, validate inputs, verify auth, and return least data necessary.
- Do not create duplicate mutation paths if form actions already fit the use case.
- Use consistent response formats within the project.
- Protect webhook routes with signature verification when relevant.
- Make webhook handlers idempotent when possible.
